modules.description: Provides functions to read button states, axis positions, and rumble effects from a gamepad device. Operates on raw input data structures representing controller inputs and output configurations. Used to implement real-time player input handling and haptic feedback in game applications.

Handles input polling and event processing from gamepad devices. Processes axis values, button states, and device connection status. Used to map controller inputs to in-game actions like movement, shooting, and menu navigation.
